{"_id":"class-paladin","name":"Paladin","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/shield.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Paladins are holy warriors bound to lawful good. They smite evil, lay on hands to heal, and gain a special mount. Their code requires honor, respect for authority, and punishing those who harm innocents.</p><h3>Alignment</h3><p>Lawful good only.</p><h3>Key Class Features</h3><ul><li><strong>Smite Evil:</strong> Once per day (more at 5th, 10th, 15th, 20th), add Cha to attack and 1 point of damage per paladin level on one melee attack vs. evil.</li><li><strong>Divine Grace (2nd):</strong> Add Charisma bonus to all saving throws.</li><li><strong>Lay on Hands (2nd):</strong> Heal total hp per day equal to paladin level Ã— Cha bonus; alternatively deal that damage to undead with a touch attack.</li><li><strong>Aura of Courage (3rd):</strong> Immune to fear; allies within 10 ft. gain +4 morale on saves vs. fear.</li><li><strong>Turn Undead (4th):</strong> As a cleric of three levels lower.</li><li><strong>Spells (4th):</strong> Prepare and cast a small number of divine spells from the paladin list. Wisdom-based.</li><li><strong>Special Mount (5th):</strong> Call a celestial warhorse (or similar) once per day.</li></ul><p><em>Ex-paladins:</em> Willfully committing an evil act or grossly violating the code loses all paladin abilities until atonement. Gaining a level in any other class prevents further paladin advancement.</p>","hitDie":"d10","babProgression":"good","saves":{"fort":"good","ref":"poor","will":"good"},"skillPointsPerLevel":2,"classSkills":[{"key":"concentration","name":"Concentration"},{"key":"craft-alchemy","name":"Craft (Alchemy)"},{"key":"craft-armorsmithing","name":"Craft (Armorsmithing)"},{"key":"craft-bowmaking","name":"Craft (Bowmaking)"},{"key":"craft-weaponsmithing","name":"Craft (Weaponsmithing)"},{"key":"craft-trapmaking","name":"Craft (Trapsmithing)"},{"key":"diplomacy","name":"Diplomacy"},{"key":"handleAnimal","name":"Handle Animal"},{"k